{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:psalms.49",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 49,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 49 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.49.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:1",
      "text": "Hear this, all you peoples. Listen, all you inhabitants of the world,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.49.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:2",
      "text": "both low and high, rich and poor together.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.49.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:3",
      "text": "My mouth will speak words of wisdom. My heart will utter understanding.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.49.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:4",
      "text": "I will incline my ear to a proverb. I will solve my riddle on the harp.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.49.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:5",
      "text": "Why should I fear in the days of evil, when iniquity at my heels surrounds me?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.49.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:6",
      "text": "Those who trust in their wealth, and boast in the multitude of their riches—",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.49.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:7",
      "text": "none of them can by any means redeem his brother, nor give God a ransom for him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.49.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:8",
      "text": "For the redemption of their life is costly, no payment is ever enough,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.49.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:9",
      "text": "that he should live on forever, that he should not see corruption.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.49.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:10",
      "text": "For he sees that wise men die; likewise the fool and the senseless perish, and leave their wealth to others.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.49.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:11",
      "text": "Their inward thought is that their houses will endure forever, and their dwelling places to all generations. They name their lands after themselves.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.49.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:12",
      "text": "But man, despite his riches, doesn’t endure. He is like the animals that perish.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.49.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:13",
      "text": "This is the destiny of those who are foolish, and of those who approve their sayings. Selah.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.49.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:14",
      "text": "They are appointed as a flock for Sheol. Death shall be their shepherd. The upright shall have dominion over them in the morning. Their beauty shall decay in Sheol, far from their mansion.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.49.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:15",
      "text": "But God will redeem my soul from the power of Sheol, for he will receive me. Selah.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.49.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:16",
      "text": "Don’t be afraid when a man is made rich, when the glory of his house is increased;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.49.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:17",
      "text": "for when he dies he will carry nothing away. His glory won’t descend after him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.49.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:18",
      "text": "Though while he lived he blessed his soul — and men praise you when you do well for yourself—",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.49.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:19",
      "text": "he shall go to the generation of his fathers. They shall never see the light.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.49.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:20",
      "text": "A man who has riches without understanding, is like the animals that perish.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
